---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---
<div class="w-full bg-black flex justify-center items-center relative top-[-3px] max-lg:relative max-lg:top-[-3px]">
    <div class="w-full flex justify-center items-center  pl-[80px] pr-[80px] max-lg:flex-col max-lg:!px-[0px] max-lg:pt-0 ">
        <div class="w-[50%] flex justify-center items-center max-lg:w-full ">
            <div class=" w-[100%] flex justify-center items-center ">
                <div class="max-lg:w-[100%] max-lg:flex max-lg:flex-col max-lg:justify-center max-lg:items-center">
                    <div class="bg-[url('/assets/scratchy-overlay.jpeg')] bg-cover w-[90%] h-[600px] max-lg:h-[60vw] max-md:h-[400px]">
                        <div class="bg-[#000000ce] w-[100%] relative before:content-[''] before:absolute before:top-0 before:w-full before:h-full bg-custom-gradient">
                        <Image src={'https://res.cloudinary.com/dt3zbndrl/image/upload/v1740753130/myles_headshot_n0vacn.png'} width={100} height={100} format="png" alt={"Myles"}   class="w-[100%] max-lg:object-cover h-[600px] max-lg:h-[60vw] max-md:h-[400px] object-cover object-center" />
                    </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                    class="bg-black  w-[90%] flex justify-center items-center text-[22px] border-1 border-[grey]  bg-[linear-gradient(0deg,#010101,#010101),radial-gradient(68.37%_68.37%_at_50%_31.63%,rgba(173,173,173,0.2)_0%,rgba(1,1,1,0.2)_100%)]  shadow-[0px_0px_250px_20px_rgba(203,203,203,0.2)] rounded-2xl relative bottom-[130px] max-lg:bottom-[90px] after:content-[url('/assets/quotation.svg')] after:w-[80%] after:h-6 after:absolute  after:top-[-13px] max-lg:after:top-[-17px] after:left-[0px] max-lg:after:left-[-10px]"
                  >
                    <p class="w-[90%] text-[20px] text-white pb-6 pl-3 pr-3 pt-13 max-lg:text-[14px] max-lg:font-normal max-lg:leading-[18px]">
                      My high school journey seemed destined for a top D1 program—until
                      injuries hit. I lost scholarship offers, scrambled for late
                      interest, and discovered the hard way that “fit” matters more than
                      hype.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
          
        </div>
        </div>
        <div class="w-[50%] flex justify-center items-center max-lg:w-[90%]">
            <div class="w-[100%] text-white ">
                <p class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-[#9E9B9B] font-bold text-[48px] leading-16 uppercase max-lg:text-[32px] max-lg:leading-[40px]">
                    Led by Experience.</br> Designed for Results.
                </p>
                <div class="w-full flex flex-col items-center gap-6 text-[20px] mb-11 max-lg:text-[14px] max-lg:font-normal max-lg:mt-10">
                    <p>
                        I’m Myles Warren, a former D1 athlete who battled through injuries, transfers, and the struggles of recruiting firsthand. I’ve lived the frustration of being overlooked, and I know what it takes to break through the noise and secure real college opportunities. That’s why I created HoopsToCollege—to give serious athletes a competitive edge that I wish I had.
                    </p>
                  <p>
                    With direct connections to college coaches, a deep understanding of NCAA recruiting, and a proven track record of helping players maximize their offers, I’ve built a system that works. This isn’t just a program—it’s a roadmap designed for athletes who refuse to go unnoticed.
                  </p>
                </div>
              <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-start gap-3 max-lg:pb-16">
                <p class="font-semibold text-[24px] max-lg:text-[14px]">
                    Myles Warren
                </p>
                <p>
                    Founder, HoopsToCollege | Former D1 Athlete | Recruiting Expert
                </p>

              </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<style>
    .bg-custom-gradient::before {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0) 79.84%, #000000 100%),
    linear-gradient(360deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0) 76.57%, #000000 100%),
    linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0) 80.37%, #000000 102.2%),
    linear-gradient(270deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0) 83.96%, #000000 102.08%);
}

</style>